<section class="container" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="manifesto reveal">
    <h2 class="manifesto-title">Signet Is Not a Memory Service. It's a Standard.</h2>
    <p class="manifesto-body">
      We don't host your data. We don't run your queries. Signet defines how agent identity, memory, and config should be stored, carried, and surfaced between platforms. Structured memory, graph traversal, and retrieval are substrate. The real goal is a context-selection system that can get sharper over time, learn what actually helps, and forget what keeps getting in the way. YAML + Markdown in a directory you own. SQLite on your disk. An open spec anyone can implement.
    </p>
    <div class="manifesto-badges">
      <span class="manifesto-badge">Not an API</span>
      <span class="manifesto-badge">Not a Platform</span>
      <span class="manifesto-badge">Not a Service</span>
      <span class="manifesto-badge">Injection-Safe</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
